# C/C++

- Image ships `build-essential`, `cmake`, `ninja-build`, `pkg-config` — heavy science stacks belong in the project pixi/uv env.
- Prefer out-of-tree builds (`cmake -B build -G Ninja && cmake --build build`).
- For Python bindings: follow the project's existing tool (pybind11, nanobind, ctypes) — do not introduce a second binding stack.
- Debug builds: `-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug` + ASan/UBSan when chasing memory bugs.
- Before large refactors, locate symbols with `ctags -R` or `agentfindsym`, not blind file reads.
